            <p>&#34;The Hesperus&#34;¬ù<lb/>
                Magnolia&#44;<lb/>
                Mass.<lb/>
                July 23<hi rend="sup">d</hi> &#91;18&#93;84<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear M<hi rend="sup">r</hi>. Morais&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>The sad event of Mr Jacobs&#39;<lb/> death&#44; joined with your various duties&#44; make<lb/> your little delay in replying perfectly excusable.<lb/></p>
            <p>The decorated paper  for the Album came safe&#45;<lb/>ly to hand&#59; I have written out the lines&#44; and re&#45;<lb/>turn it with this.		Do not you and Nina<lb/> contribute something&#63; And if so&#44; may we<lb/> not have a glimpse of them&#63; No doubt you<lb/>  will retain copies of the same.<lb/></p>
            <p>Let me thank you for the kind wishes for our<lb/> health and pleasure during the summer. We<lb/> have thoroughly enjoyed the quiet and beauty of<lb/> this peaceful spot. Pray thank Nina also<lb/> for her friendly message.<lb/></p>
            <p>With sincere regard from all&#44;<lb/>
                Very truly yours<lb/>
                Mary M. Cohen<lb/>
            </p>
        </body>
